body:
## Summary
In `@excalidraw/excalidraw` 0.18.1, runtime font loading appears to ignore `window.EXCALIDRAW_ASSET_PATH` entirely: every registered `FontFace` sources **only** the esm.sh fallback (`…/dist/prod/fonts/…`), and the self-hosted URL is never attempted — regardless of how early the global is set.

## Environment
- @excalidraw/excalidraw **0.18.1**, React 19.2, Next.js 16 (app router, component behind `next/dynamic` with `ssr: false`), Chromium

## Setup (per docs)
- Copied `node_modules/@excalidraw/excalidraw/dist/prod/fonts` → served same-origin at `/excalidraw/fonts/…` (verified reachable).
- `window.EXCALIDRAW_ASSET_PATH` set to an **absolute** URL (`origin + '/excalidraw/'`) via an inline `<head>` script — guaranteed to execute before any bundle. (Also tried: module-scope assignment, and assignment inside the `dynamic()` loader immediately before `import()`.)

## Observed
- DevTools network: **zero** requests to the same-origin font path; all font fetches go to `https://esm.sh/@excalidraw/excalidraw@0.18.1/dist/prod/fonts/…` (in one session with a strict CSP we counted 230 blocked CDN attempts).
- `window.EXCALIDRAW_ASSET_PATH` verified present & correct in the page at the time fonts load.
- Font faces are (re-)registered lazily per text render, so late assignment isn't the explanation — the global was set before chunk evaluation in all attempts.
- Reading `dist/prod/chunk-K2UTITRG.js`: `getFontFaceUrls` does push `new URL(rel, normalizeBaseUrl(window.EXCALIDRAW_ASSET_PATH))` ahead of `ASSETS_FALLBACK_URL`, but runtime behavior suggests that branch never engages for the runtime-registered faces.

## Impact
Under a CSP with `font-src 'self'` (or in offline/self-hosted environments), all handwriting fonts silently degrade to system fonts, and consoles fill with CSP violations.

## Workaround (for anyone else hitting this)
Patch the constructor before the Excalidraw chunk loads and rewrite CDN sources to a self-hosted font:
```ts
const Orig = window.FontFace;
window.FontFace = class extends Orig {
  constructor(family, source, desc) {
    if (typeof source === 'string' && source.includes('esm.sh/@excalidraw')) {
      super(family, "url(/fonts/your-font.woff2) format('woff2')", { ...desc, weight: '100 900' });
    } else super(family, source, desc);
  }
};
```
Happy to provide more traces if useful — and sorry in advance if we're holding it wrong; the docs pattern above is what we followed.
